<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Query the ScavHunt List</title>
  </head>

  <body>
    <h1>The F.I.S.T. Database Search</h1>
    <P>Here you have the opportunity to execute searches on the ScavHunt list. There are several options for doing this: you can search for a keyword, list items by category, see a given user's items, or view a particular item number.</P>
    <HR>
    <h2>Key Word Search</h2>
    <form action="getquery.pl" method="get">
      <input type="hidden" name="type" value="keyword">
      <input type="hidden" name="source" value="query.html">
      <P>Keyword or phrase (exact matches only):
	<input type="text" size="40" name="key"></P>
      <P>Sort By:
      <SELECT name="sort">
	<option selected value="index">Item Number</option>
	<option value="points">Point Value</option>
	<option value="status">Item Status</option>
      </SELECT>
      </P>
      <input type="submit" value="Search">
    </form>

    <HR>
    <h2>Category Listing</h2>
    <form action="getquery.pl" method="get">
      <input type="hidden" name="type" value="catsort">
      <input type="hidden" name="source" value="query.html">
      
      <P>Category:
	<SELECT name="cat">
	  <option value="food">Food</option>
	  <option value="project">Projects</option>
	  <option value="event">Events</option>
	  <option value="trip">Roadtrip!</option>
	  <option value="perform">Performance</option>
	  <option value="craft">Crafts</option>
	  <option value="thing">Thing</option>
	  <option value="trivia">Trivia</option>
	  <option value="misc">Miscellaneous</option>
	  <option value="olympics">ScavOlympics!</option>
          <option value="av">Audio/Video</option>
          <option value="winter">WinterSports</option>
	  <option selected value="all">All</option>
	</SELECT>
      </P>
      <P>Sort By:
	<SELECT name="sort">
	  <option selected value="index">Item Number</option>
	  <option value="points">Point Value</option>
	  <option value="status">Item Status</option>
	</SELECT>
      </P>
      <input type="submit" value="Search"><P>
    </form>

    <HR>
    <h2>User Search</h2>
    <form action="User.pl" method="get">

      <!--   <MAGIC>   -->

      <input type="submit" value="Display User">
    </form>

    <HR>
    <h2>View Item by Number</h2>
    <form action="getquery.pl" method="get">
      <input type="hidden" name="type" value="index">
      <input type="hidden" name="source" value="query.html">
      Item number to edit: 
      <input type="text" size="10" name="index">&nbsp;
      <input type="submit">
    </form>

    <hr>
    <address><a href="mailto:mbmillig@midway.uchicago.edu">Michael Milligan</a></address>

  </body>
</html>
